<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870213-0097 </DOCNO><HL> Blount Unit Gets Job</HL><DD> 02/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BLTB EFAC </IN><DATELINE> MONTGOMERY, Ala.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Blount Inc. said its BlountConstructors division received a $44 million contract fromThermo Power andamp; Electric Inc.   Terms call for the unit to provide engineering, procurement and construction for a gas-fired cogeneration plant in Greeley, Colo. Thermo Power is a subsidiary of San Diego-based Energy Factors, which has interests in energy cogeneration. </TEXT></DOC>